00:00:00.410 --> 00:00:01.756
- [Instructor] At a barbecue to celebrate

00:00:01.756 --> 00:00:03.867
the end of the soccer season,

00:00:03.867 --> 00:00:06.117
1,354 hot dogs were served.

00:00:08.409 --> 00:00:10.533
Round the number of hot dogs

00:00:10.533 --> 00:00:12.033
to the nearest 10.

00:00:13.093 --> 00:00:17.010
Alright, let me just
rewrite the number, 1,354.

00:00:18.701 --> 00:00:22.102
Now let's just remember our places.

00:00:22.102 --> 00:00:22.935
I could write it like that.

00:00:22.935 --> 00:00:23.775
This is the ones.

00:00:23.775 --> 00:00:25.191
This is the tens.

00:00:25.191 --> 00:00:27.007
This is the hundreds place,

00:00:27.007 --> 00:00:30.491
and this is the thousands place.

00:00:30.491 --> 00:00:33.138
Now they want to round
the number of hot dogs

00:00:33.138 --> 00:00:34.618
to the nearest 10.

00:00:34.618 --> 00:00:36.790
So round it to the nearest 10 here,

00:00:36.790 --> 00:00:38.665
and so right now we have five tens,

00:00:38.665 --> 00:00:39.652
but in order to round,

00:00:39.652 --> 00:00:41.824
we have to look to the
next smallest place,

00:00:41.824 --> 00:00:43.432
so we'll look to the ones,

00:00:43.432 --> 00:00:45.470
and we have four ones here,

00:00:45.470 --> 00:00:48.999
and so because this
number is less than five,

00:00:48.999 --> 00:00:50.809
so because this is less than five,

00:00:50.809 --> 00:00:52.103
we round down.

00:00:52.103 --> 00:00:53.603
So less than five,

00:00:56.000 --> 00:00:57.510
so we're gonna round down.

00:00:57.510 --> 00:00:59.010
If you round down,

00:01:01.282 --> 00:01:03.981
you get to exactly five tens,

00:01:03.981 --> 00:01:05.398
or you say 1,350.

00:01:08.955 --> 00:01:11.256
We have rounded to the nearest 10,

00:01:11.256 --> 00:01:12.506
1,350 hot dogs.

00:01:14.819 --> 00:01:17.246
Let's do another one.

